<item>
            <title>[LU-15220] Linux kernel 5.14 support</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15220</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Main changes needed to support Linux kernel 5.14 include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;__set_page_dirty() is no longer exported&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;idmapped mounts support, which adds &apos;struct user_namespace *&apos; to all VFS operations (since kernel 5.12)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&apos;/* fallthrough */&apos; hits implicit-fallthrough error with gcc version 11. Using the pseudo keyword &apos;fallthrough&apos; to resolve the issue&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;needs to import namespace CRYPTO_INTERNAL (since kernel 5.12)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
