                            <comment id="321483" author="paf0186" created="Thu, 23 Dec 2021 15:46:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jian,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oof, this is actually pretty complicated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see Neil changed the code here with &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/40827/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/40827/&lt;/a&gt; .&#160; That basically makes this function pointless in these kernels - the entire point is to avoid taking the xarray lock for each page...&#160; Hmm.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OK, here is my suggested solution for compatibility, since we have already lost the desired xarray lock behavior.&#160; I will look at restoring that, but in the meantime:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For kernels which do not have account_page_dirtied, which should also include kernels which do not have __set_page_dirty, the right thing to do is replace all of the code in vvp_set_pagevec_dirty with a loop calling __set_page_dirty_nobuffers on the pages in the pagevec.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
